{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μήποτε</b> <br /> or <b>μή ποτε</b>, <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>μή κοτε</b> (see. below 11): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> as <i>adverb</i> <b>never, on no account</b>, after ὡς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 205, “Eu.” 882 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; after εἰ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ch.” 182, etc.\">Refs</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eu.” 977, “Supp.” 617 \">Refs</a>]; especially in oaths, <b>never</b>, ὀμοῦμαι, μή ποτε τῆς εὐνῆς ἐπιβήμεναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.133, 275; ἐπεκέκλετ᾽ Ἐρινῦς, μή ποτε.. ἐφέσσεσθαι [prev. work] 455 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; in aposiopesis, ἢ μήπορ᾽ ἆρ᾽.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 97: in indirect speech, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 86. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> in prohibition or warning, with <i>aorist</i> <i>subjunctive</i>, μή ποτε καὶ σὺ.. ὀλέσσῃς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.81, etc.: with \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i> for <i>imperative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.441. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> in later Gr., <b>perhaps</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1172a33, LXX.Gen.24.5, Aristeas 15, 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.13, 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 3.22.80, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.106d, 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 18.4. \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> as <i>conjunction</i>, <b>lest ever</b>, αἰσχυνόμενοι φάτιν ἀνδρῶν.., μή ποτέ τις εἴπῃσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.324, +others; οὐδαμὰ ἐλπίσας μή κοτε ἄρα.. ἐλάσῃ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.77, compare 8.53. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3379","accentedUnicode":"μήποτε","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3361","matchingForm":"μή","stepTransliteration":"mē","gloss":"not","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不, 不要, 不可","_es_Gloss":"no","_zh_Gloss":"不, 不要, 不可"},{"strongNumber":"G4218","matchingForm":"ποτέ","stepTransliteration":"pote","gloss":"once/when","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從前","_es_Gloss":"una vez/cuando","_zh_Gloss":"从前"}],"shortDef":"lest","mediumDef":"never, otherwise, that... not; can function as an adverb, <b>BDAG</b> lists it as a negative <i>particle</i>, <i>conjunction</i>, and interrogative <i>participle</i>, same signif. and usage as <greek>μή</greek>, <ref='Mat.4.6; 13:15'>Mt. 4:6; 13:15</ref>; <ref='Heb.9.17'>Heb. 9:17;</ref> also, <b>whether,</b> <ref='Luk.3.15'>Lk. 3:15</ref>","stepGloss":"lest","stepTransliteration":"mēpote","count":0,"_es_Definition":"(1) conj. por temor de que, para que no, que.. no, de no ser así ; (2) interrog. partícula: si quizá, tal vez; (3) nunca (HEB.9.17)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 從不 (來 9:17) <br>2) 以致...不...<br>3) 也許, 是否<br>4) 可能 (太 25:9)","_zh_Definition":"1) 从不 (来 9:17) <br>2) 以致...不...<br>3) 也许, 是否<br>4) 可能 (太 25:9)","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"meaning\",\"G4218\",\"once/when\",54,\"ποτέ\"],[\"combination\",\"G3379\",\"lest\",0,\"μήποτε\"]]","_vi_Definition":"kẻo e; e không","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恐怕","_es_Gloss":"para que no","_zh_Gloss":"恐怕"}]}